s than I do!\\\"\", \"from\": 2786, \"to\": 2875, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"terms\", \"from\": 2806, \"to\": 2811}, {\"ngram\": \"numbers\", \"from\": 2815, \"to\": 2822}, {\"ngram\": \"quite a few better colours\", \"from\": 2837, \"to\": 2863}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another trip to the top step of the podium for Guy and Dean moved them level with Adam Peaty as the most successful British Olympic swimmers of all-time on three gold medals.\", \"from\": 2877, \"to\": 3051, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2932, \"end\": 2936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dean_Winchester\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 2.3835523901084794e-12, \"text\": \"Dean\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dean_Winchester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dean_Winchester\"}, {\"begin\": 2959, \"end\": 2969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}, {\"begin\": 2993, \"end\": 3000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.7297532113326731, \"rank\": 0.18495243458555305, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Another trip\", \"from\": 2877, \"to\": 2889}, {\"ngram\": \"the top step\", \"from\": 2893, \"to\": 2905}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 2909, \"to\": 2919}, {\"ngram\": \"Guy\", \"from\": 2924, \"to\": 2927}, {\"ngram\": \"level\", \"from\": 2948, \"to\": 2953}, {\"ngram\": \"all-time\", \"from\": 3021, \"to\": 3029}, {\"ngram\": \"three gold medals\", \"from\": 3033, \"to\": 3050}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Remarkably, Guy had broken his nine-year-old per